cs.CR, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.AI, cs.SE 

This paper is primarily focused on detecting and preventing cyber attacks in IoT networks using SDN-based in-network Honeypot. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also discusses the use of SDN, which falls under the category of cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). Additionally, the paper proposes a solution to preemptively disrupt and mislead attacks, which can be categorized under cs.SY (Systems and Control). The use of intelligent spoofing and adding misleading information to network traffic can also be related to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.SE (Software Engineering).
